==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: go-cart
<hw>go"-cart`</hw></mhw> <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A framework moving on casters, designed to support
children while learning to walk.</def> <wns>[wns=1]</wns>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> walker, baby-walker.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A cart used to carry heavy items and pushed by a
person; it may have one, two or four wheels.</def>
<wns>[wns=2]</wns>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> handcart, pushcart, cart.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>a small carriage in which a baby or child is pushed
around.</def> <wns>[wns=3]</wns>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> baby buggy, baby carriage, perambulator, pram,
stroller, pushchair, pusher.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>God</ent>⟦br⟧
